---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const faqItems = [
  { q: "Do you have a support Discord?", a: "Join our Discord server at discord.gg/TnhxcqynZ2." },
  { q: "Will I get banned for using this?", a: "You are breaking Discord ToS by using Legcord, but no one has been banned from using it or any of the client mods included." },
  { q: "Can I use this on anything other than AArch64?", a: "Yes! Legcord should work normally under Windows, macOS, and Linux as long as it has Electron support." },
  { q: "How can I access the settings?", a: "There should be a Settings button in your Discord settings with Legcord settings. Alternatively you can open Legcord settings from the tray icon." },
  { q: "How does this work?", a: "We utilize the official Discord web app and package it within Electron. We provide seamless integration for loading themes and mods without installers or injectors, with optimizations for a smooth experience." },
  { q: "Can Legcord block YouTube ads?", a: "Yes, Legcord by default blocks YouTube ads found in embeds and WatchTogether." },
  { q: "Can I stream screenshare audio with it?", a: "Legcord only supports screensharing audio on Windows and Linux. Linux requires PulseAudio or PipeWire." },
  { q: "Where can I find the source code?", a: "The source code is on GitHub at github.com/Legcord/Legcord." },
  { q: "Where can I translate this?", a: "Translations are done using our Weblate page at hosted.weblate.org/projects/legcord/legcord." },
  { q: "Does Legcord have a privacy policy?", a: "Yes, you can find it at legcord.app/privacy.txt." },
  { q: "How do I update Legcord?", a: "Legcord can check for updates automatically. You can also get the latest build from the download page or GitHub releases." },
  { q: "How do I uninstall Legcord?", a: "Remove it like any other app using your system's uninstaller. Your Discord account and data are unchanged." },
  { q: "What's the difference between Shelter and Vencord?", a: "Both are client mods. Shelter comes pre-installed with Legcord; Vencord is togglable in settings and offers a large plugin ecosystem. Use one at a time." },
  { q: "Does Legcord work on Steam Deck / Raspberry Pi?", a: "Legcord supports Linux on x64 and AArch64. Steam Deck and Raspberry Pi can use the Linux build on compatible distros." },
];

const faqJsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: faqItems.map(({ q, a }) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    name: q,
    acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: a },
  })),
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ – Legcord"
  description="Frequently asked questions about Legcord: download, install, update, plugins, Linux, Mac, Windows, Steam Deck, and more."
  canonical="/faq"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqJsonLd)} />
  </Fragment>
  <article class="bg-gray-900 py-16" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <header class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 id="faq-heading" class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Answers to common questions about the Legcord Discord client: installation, updates, plugins, system requirements, and support.
        </p>
      </header>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Do you have a support Discord?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300"><a href="https://discord.gg/TnhxcqynZ2" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Join our Discord server</a></p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Will I get banned for using this?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">You are breaking <a href='https://discord.com/terms#software-in-discord%E2%80%99s-services' class='text-blue-400 hover:underline'>Discord ToS</a> by using Legcord, but no one has been banned from using it or any of the client mods included.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Can I use this on anything other than AArch64?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Yes! Legcord should work normally under Windows, macOS, and Linux as long as it has Electron support.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">How can I access the settings?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">There should be a <strong>Settings</strong> button in your Discord settings with Legcord settings. Alternatively you can open Legcord settings from the tray icon.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">How does this work?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">We utilize the official Discord web app and package it within Electron. While this approach may seem familiar, our focus is on delivering a truly customized and enhanced experience. Unlike many others, we provide seamless integration for loading themes and mods without the need for installers or injectors. You can easily enable transparency effects and adopt Windows' Fluent Design, offering a modern and sleek interface. Though it's fundamentally a web wrapper, we have implemented numerous optimizations and patches to ensure a smooth and tailored experience for you.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Can Legcord block YouTube ads?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Yes, Legcord by default blocks YouTube ads found in embeds and WatchTogether!</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Can I stream screenshare audio with it?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Legcord only supports screensharing audio on Windows and <strong>Linux</strong>. Linux requires you to have either PulseAudio installed or PipeWire.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Where can I find the source code?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">The source code is on <a href="https://github.com/Legcord/Legcord/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">GitHub</a>.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Where can I translate this?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Translations are done using our <a href="https://hosted.weblate.org/projects/legcord/legcord/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Weblate page</a>.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Does Legcord have a privacy policy?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">You can find it <a href="https://legcord.app/privacy.txt" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">here</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">How do I update Legcord?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Legcord can check for updates automatically. You'll see a notification when a new version is available—click it to download and install. You can also grab the latest build from the <a href="/download" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">download page</a> or <a href="https://github.com/Legcord/Legcord/releases" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">GitHub releases</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">How do I uninstall Legcord?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Remove it like any other app: use your system's uninstaller (e.g. Settings → Apps on Windows, or drag to Trash on macOS). Your Discord account and data are unchanged—they're tied to your account, not the client.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What's the difference between Shelter and Vencord?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Both are client mods (plugins) you can use with Legcord. <strong>Shelter</strong> comes pre-installed with Legcord and is lightweight. <strong>Vencord</strong> is togglable in Legcord settings and offers a large plugin ecosystem. You can enable one or the other (or neither) in Legcord settings. See the <a href="/plugins" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Plugins page</a> for links.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Does Legcord work on Steam Deck / Raspberry Pi?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Legcord supports Linux on x64 and AArch64. On <strong>Steam Deck</strong> (Arch-based), you can install the Linux build if Electron is supported. On <strong>Raspberry Pi</strong> and other ARM devices, the AArch64 Linux build should work on compatible distros.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>